  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation of Copper Mining Industry</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project objectives are as folllows: i)    To rehabilitate key equipment and introduce new technology in the Nakana smelter and Acid Plant. ii)    To modernize the concentrator at Nchanga to improve metallurgical performance. iii)    To restore Scaw Fondry rated capacities in millballs and machine parts. iv)    To provide local and overseas training to employees in operation and maintenance. 1.  Overall Objective: ----------------- To increase copper production and lower operational costs. 2.  Specific Objectives: ------------------- To begin upgrading the operations through modernization and introduction of new technology.</narrative>
  </description>
